<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="620" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-07-26"><hi rend="italic">July 26,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Adee acknowledges the receipt of Mr. Powell’s two telegrams, and
                            says that the rule as to piracy is stated in instruction of December 15,
                            1883, to Mr. Langston, Mr. Powell’s predecessor.)</p>
                    </div>
